# Cursor rules — stevedores-org/aivcs-human-in-the-loop

Read `AGENTS.md` for the canonical contract. The rules below are the
operational subset for Cursor:

- aivcs human-in-the-loop UI. Stack: TypeScript + React + Vite, runtime is
  Bun. No npm / pnpm / yarn / node. Lockfile is `bun.lockb`.
- PR base is `develop`. Never `main`.
- No secrets in git. Use ESO + GCP Secret Manager. References only.
  `.gitleaks.toml` enforces it.
- No `Dockerfile`. OCI images come from `dockworker.ai` (Step C / #6).
- No Helm. Kubernetes workload delivery is Kustomize overlays under
  `k8s/{base,overlays/dev,overlays/prod}` (Step C / #6).
- Pre-push: run `local-ci` (fallback:
  `bun run tsc --noEmit && bun run eslint . && bun test && bun run build`).
  If red, do not push.
- Conventional-Commits PR titles only. Allowed types: `feat`, `fix`,
  `chore`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `perf`, `ci`, `build`, `revert`.
- High-blast actions (force-push to `develop` / `main`, branch-protection
  bootstrap, direct cloud-API mutation): ask before applying.
- No emojis. No comments explaining what the code does — explain *why*
  when a value is non-obvious (deliberate pin, workaround, hidden
  invariant).
